
# MLOps-with-CML-and-DVC-Bike-Sharing-Demand-predict
Experimenting MLOPS with CML and DVC for the kaggle Bike sharing prediction problem. 

##	Vidéo tutorial 1:

[MLOps Tutorial #1: Intro to Continuous Integration for ML](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9BgIDqAzfuA)


-   Create a GITHUB REPO
-   Create a requirements.txt file
-   Create a Train.py file with data preparation, train test split, modeling, creation of a metrics.txt file, plotings some result and plot to check the modeling performance

Then we create .github/workflows/cml.YAML

Here we discribe our  github actions and with wich runner (COMPUTER) they will be executed.

Then we can edit the cml.YAML to create a visual markdown report  with ploting and metrics

## Vidéo tutorial 2
[MLOps Tutorial #2: When data is too big for Git](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kZKAuShWF0s)

Setting up a DVC process so the BIG DATASET is store on GDRIVE (OR S3 OR GCP) instead of github.
Step:

 - Init dvc   
 - Setup gdrive with dvc       
 - Add the csv to drive with dvc       
 - Add a   dvc pull velo.csv in cml.YAML    
 - Done !


## Vidéo tutorial 3
[MLOps Tutorial #3: Track ML models with Git & GitHub Actions](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xPncjKH6SPk)

![](data:image/png;base64,)

We create a pipeline with DVC
And at each push on github the pipeline is executed and the result of the new model is automatically compared with the metrics of the previous model.

For that we create the pipeline in dvc.yaml
And we update also cml.yaml to match with the new routine
To create a pipeline we also have two .py instead of one.
prep_data.py and train.py
